llapsed\" style=\"font-size:90%\"\n|-\n!colspan=\"7\"|'''International appearances and goals'''<ref>[http://www.rsssf.com/miscellaneous/greaves-intlg.html Jimmy Greaves \u2013 Goals in International Matches] rsssf.com</ref>\n|-\n! # !! Date !! Venue !! Opponent !! Result !! Competition !! Goal(s)\n|-\n| colspan=\"7\" style=\"text-align:center;\"|'''1959'''\n|-\n| align=center|1\n| 17 May\n| [[Estadio Nacional del Per\u00fa|Estadio Nacional]], Lima\n| {{fb|Peru}}\n| align=center|1\u20134\n| Friendly\n| 1\n|-\n| align=center|2\n| 24 May\n| [[Estadio Ol\u00edmpico Universitario]], Mexico City\n| {{fb|Mexico}}\n| align=center|1\u20132\n| Friendly\n| \n|-\n| align=center|3\n| 28 May\n| [[Wrigley Field (Los Angeles)|Wrigley Field]], Los Angeles\n| {{fb|United States}}\n| align=center|8\u20131\n| Friendly\n| \n|-\n| align=center|4\n| 17 October\n| [[Ninian Park]], [[Cardiff]]\n| {{fb|Wales}}\n| align=center|1\u20131\n| [[1959\u201360 British Home Championship]]\n| 1\n|-\n| align=center|5\n| 28 October\n| [[Wembley Stadium (1923)|Wembley Stadium]], London\n| {{fb|Sweden}}\n| align=center|2\u20133\n| Friendly\n| \n|-\n| colspan=\"7\" style=\"text-align:center;\"|'''1960'''\n|-\n| align=center|6\n| 11 May\n| [[Wembley Stadium (1923)|Wembley Stadium]], London\n| {{fb|Yugoslavia}}\n| align=center|3\u20133\n| Friendly\n| 1\n|-\n| align=center|7\n| 15 May\n| [[Santiago Bernab\u00e9u Stadium]], Madrid\n| {{fb|Spain|1945}}\n| align=center|0\u20133\n| Friendly\n| \n|-\n| align=center|8\n| 8 October\n| [[Windsor Park]], [[Belfast]]\n| {{fb|Northern Ireland}}\n| align=center|5\u20132\n| [[1960\u201361 British Home Championship]]\n| 2\n|-\n| align=center|9\n| 19 October\n| [[Stade Josy Barthel|Stade Municipale]], [[Luxembourg (city)|Luxembourg]]\n| {{fb|Luxembourg}}\n| align=center|8\u20130\n| [[1962 FIFA World Cup qualification (UEFA \u2013 Group 6)|1962 World Cup qualifier]]\n| 3\n|-\n| align=center|10\n| 26 October\n| [[Wembley Stadium (1923)|Wembley Stadium]], London\n| {{fb|Spain|1945}}\n| align=center|4\u20132\n| Friendly\n| 1\n|-\n| align=center|11\n| 23 November\n| [[Wembley Stadium (1923)|Wembley Stadium]], London\n| {{fb|Wales}}\n| align=center|5\u20131\n| [[1960\u201361 British Home Championship]]\n| 2\n|-\n| colspan=\"7\" style=\"text-align:center;\"|'''1961'''\n|-\n| align=center|12\n| 15 April\n| [[Wembley Stadium (1923)|Wembley Stadium]], London\n| {{fb|Scotland}}\n| align=center|9\u20133\n| [[1960\u201361 British Home Championship]]\n| 3\n|-\n| align=center|13\n| 21 May\n| [[Est\u00e1dio Nacional]], [[Oeiras, Portugal|Oeiras]]\n| {{fb|Portugal}}\n| align=center|1\u20131\n| [[1962 FIFA World Cup qualification (UEFA \u2013 Group 6)|1962 World Cup qualifier]]\n| \n|-\n| align=center|14\n| 24 May\n| [[Stadio Olimpico]], Rome\n| {{fb|Italy}}\n| align=center|2\u20133\n| Friendly\n| 1\n|-\n| align=center|15\n| 27 May\n| [[Ernst-Happel-Stadion|Praterstadion]], Vienna\n| {{fb|Austria}}\n| align=center|1\u20133\n| Friendly\n| 1\n|-\n| colspan=\"7\" style=\"text-align:center;\"|'''1962'''\n|-\n| align=center|16\n| 14 April\n| [[Hampden Park]], Glasgow\n| {{fb|Scotland}}\n| align=center|0\u20132\n| [[1961\u201362 British Home Championship]]\n| \n|-\n| align=center|17\n| 9 May\n| [[Wembley Stadium (1923)|Wembley Stadium]], London\n| {{fb|Switzerland}}\n| align=center|3\u20131\n| Friendly\n| \n|-\n| align=center|18\n| 20 May\n| [[Estadio Nacional del Per\u00fa|Estadio Nacional]], Lima\n| {{fb|Peru}}\n| align=center|4\u20130\n| Friendly\n| 3\n|-\n| align=center|19\n| 31 May\n| [[Estadio El Teniente|Estadio Braden]], [[Rancagua]]\n| {{fb|Hungary}}\n| align=center|1\u20132\n| [[1962 FIFA World Cup]]\n| \n|-\n| align=center|20\n| 2 June\n| [[Estadio El Teniente|Estadio Braden]], [[Rancagua]]\n| {{fb|Argentina}}\n| align=center|3\u20131\n| [[1962 FIFA World Cup]]\n| 1\n|-\n| align=center|21\n| 7 June\n| [[Estadio El Teniente|Estadio Braden]], [[Rancagua]]\n| {{fb|Bulgaria|1946}}\n| align=center|0\u20130\n| [[1962 FIFA World Cup]]\n| \n|-\n| align=center|22\n| 10 June \t\n| [[Estadio Sausalito]], [[Vi\u00f1a del Mar]]\n| {{fb|Brazil}}\n| align=center|1\u20133\n| [[1962 FIFA World Cup]]\n| \n|-\n| align=center|23\n| 3 October\n| [[Hillsborough Stadium]], [[Sheffield]]\n| {{fb|France}}\n| align=center|1\u20131\n| [[1964 European Nations' Cup qualifying]]\n| \n|-\n| align=center|24\n| 20 October\n| [[Windsor Park]], [[Belfast]]\n| {{fb|Northern Ireland}}\n| align=center|3\u20131\n| [[1962\u201363 British Home Championship]]\n| 1\n|-\n| align=center|25\n| 21 November\n| [[Wembley Stadium (1923)|Wembley Stadium]], London\n| {{fb|Wales}}\n| align=center|4\u20130\n| [[1962\u201363 British Home Championship]]\n| 1\n|-\n| colspan=\"7\" style=\"text-align:center;\"|'''1963'''\n|-\n| align=center|26\n| 27 February\n| [[Parc des Princes]], Paris\n| {{fb|France}}\n| align=center|2\u20135\n| [[1964 European Nations' Cup qualifying]]\n| \n|-\n| align=center|27\n| 6 April\n| [[Wembley Stadium (1923)|Wembley Stadium]], London\n| {{fb|Scotland}}\n| align=center|1\u20132\n| [[1962\u201363 British Home Championship]]\n| \n|-\n| align=center|28\n| 8 May\n| [[Wembley Stadium (1923)|Wembley Stadium]], London\n| {{fb|Brazil}}\n| align=center|1\u20131\n| Friendly\n| \n|-\n| align=center|29\n| 29 May\n| [[Teheln\u00e9 pole]], [[Bratislava]]\n| {{fb|Czechoslovakia}}\n| align=center|4\u20132\n| Friendly\n| 2\n|-\n| align=center|30\n| 5 June\n| [[St. Jakob Stadium]], [[Basel]]\n| {{fb|Switzerland}}\n| align=center|8\u20131\n| Friendly\n| \n|-\n| align=center|31\n| 12 October\n| [[Ninian Park]], [[Cardiff]]\n| {{fb|Wales}}\n| align=center|4\u20130\n| [[1963\u201364 British Home Championship]]\n| 1\n|-\n| align=center|32\n| 23 October\n| [[Wembley Stadium (1923)|Wembley Stadium]], London\n| Rest of World\n| align=center|2\u20131\n| Friendly\n| 1\n|-\n| align=center|33\n| 20 November\n| [[Wembley Stadium (1923)|Wembley Stadium]], London\n| {{fb|Northern Ireland}}\n| align=center|8\u20133\n| [[1963\u201364 British Home Championship]]\n| 4\n|-\