ory}} || \"Nine Last Days on Planet Earth\" || ''[[Tor.com]]''\n|align=\"center\"| <ref name=\"Hugo19\"/>\n|-\n| {{sortname|Brooke|Bolander}} || {{sort|\"Only Harmless Great Thing\"|\"[[The Only Harmless Great Thing]]\"}} || [[Tor.com|Tor.com Publishing]]\n|align=\"center\"| <ref name=\"Hugo19\"/>\n|-\n| {{sortname|Naomi|Kritzer}} || {{sort|\"Thing About Ghost Stories\"|\"[[The Thing About Ghost Stories]]\"}} || ''[[Uncanny Magazine]]''\n|align=\"center\"| <ref name=\"Hugo19\"/>\n|-\n| {{sortname|Simone|Heller|nolink=1}} || \"When We Were Starless\" || ''[[Clarkesworld Magazine]]''\n|align=\"center\"| <ref name=\"Hugo19\"/>\n|-\n!scope=\"row\" align=\"center\" rowspan=\"6\" style=\"font-weight:normal;\"| [[2019 in literature|2020]]\n| {{sortname|Caroline M. | Yoachim}} || {{sort|\"Archronology of Love\"|\"The Archronology of Love\"}} || ''[[Lightspeed Magazine]]''\n|align=\"center\"| <ref name=\"Hugo20\"/>\n|-\n| {{sortname|Sarah|Gailey}} || \"Away With the Wolves\" || ''[[Uncanny Magazine]]''\n|align=\"center\"| <ref name=\"Hugo20\"/>\n|-\n| {{sortname|Sarah|Pinsker}} || {{sort|\"Blur in the Corner of Your Eye\"|\"The Blur in the Corner of Your Eye\"}} || ''[[Uncanny Magazine]]''\n|align=\"center\"| <ref name=\"Hugo20\"/>\n|-\n| {{sortname|N. K.|Jemisin}} || {{sort|\"Emergency Skin\"|''Emergency Skin''}} || [[Amazon.com]]\n|align=\"center\"| <ref name=\"Hugo20\"/>\n|-\n| Siobhan Carroll || \"For He Can Creep\" || ''[[Tor.com]]''\n|align=\"center\"| <ref name=\"Hugo20\"/>\n|-\n| {{sortname|Ted|Chiang}} || \"Omphalos\" || ''[[Exhalation: Stories]]'' ([[Alfred A. Knopf.]]) \n|align=\"center\"| <ref name=\"Hugo20\"/>\n|}\n\n=== Retro Hugos ===\nBeginning with the [[54th World Science Fiction Convention|1996 Worldcon]], the World Science Fiction Society created the concept of \"Retro Hugos\", in which the Hugo award could be retroactively awarded for years 50, 75, or 100 years before the current year, if no awards were originally given that year.<ref name=\"thafaq\"/> Retro Hugos have been awarded eight times, for 1939, 1941, 1943\u20141946, 1951, and 1954.<ref group=\"Note\" name=\"RETRO\"/><ref name=\"LocusRetroHugoinfo\"/>\n\n{| class=\"sortable wikitable\" width=\"85%\" cellpadding=\"5\" style=\"margin: 1em auto 1em auto\"\n|-\n! width=\"7%\" scope=\"col\"|Year\n! width=\"7%\" scope=\"col\"|Year awarded\n! width=\"21%\" scope=\"col\"|Author(s)\n! width=\"35%\" scope=\"col\"|Novelette\n! width=\"26%\" scope=\"col\"|Publisher or publication\n! width=\"4%\" scope=\"col\" class=\"unsortable\"|Ref.\n|- style=\"background:#B0C4DE;\"\n!scope=\"row\" align=\"center\" rowspan=\"5\" style=\"font-weight:normal;\"| [[1938 in literature|1939]]\n!align=\"center\" rowspan=\"5\" style=\"font-weight:normal;\"| 2014\n| {{sortname|Clifford D.|Simak}}* || \"[[Rule 18]]\" || ''[[Analog Science Fiction and Fact|Astounding Science-Fiction]]''\n|align=\"center\"| <ref name=\"Hugo39\"/>\n|-\n| {{sortname|John W.|Campbell}} || \"Dead Knowledge\" || ''[[Analog Science Fiction and Fact|Astounding Stories]]''\n|align=\"center\"| <ref name=\"Hugo39\"/>\n|-\n| {{sortname|Henry|Kuttner}} || \"Hollywood on the Moon\" || ''[[Wonder Stories|Thrilling Wonder Stories]]''\n|align=\"center\"| <ref name=\"Hugo39\"/>\n|-\n| {{sortname|Robert E.|Howard}} || \"[[Pigeons from Hell]]\" || ''[[Weird Tales]]''\n|align=\"center\"| <ref name=\"Hugo39\"/>\n|-\n| {{sortname|C. L.|Moore}} || \"Werewoman\" || ''Leaves''\n|align=\"center\"| <ref name=\"Hugo39\"/>\n|- style=\"background:#B0C4DE;\"\n!scope=\"row\" align=\"center\" rowspan=\"5\" style=\"font-weight:normal;\"| [[1940 in literature|1941]]\n!align=\"center\" rowspan=\"5\" style=\"font-weight:normal;\"| 2016\n| {{sortname|Robert A.|Heinlein}}* || {{sort|\"Roads Must Roll\"|\"[[The Roads Must Roll]]\"}} || ''[[Analog Science Fiction and Fact|Astounding Science Fiction]]''\n|align=\"center\"| <ref name=\"Hugo41\"/>\n|-\n| {{sortname|Robert A.|Heinlein}} || \"[[Blowups Happen]]\" || ''[[Analog Science Fiction and Fact|Asto